   	<sect1 id="simple_test">
   	<title>Simple test</title>    
   		<para>
    		To test your <application>POD</application> installation you can use a simple test provided with the distributive
    		(see the test directory in your <application>POD</application> installation folder). The test performs a simple ROOT analysis.
    		</para>
    		<para>
    		It is also recommended to make several copies of the root file,
    		like <filename>test/dstarmb1.root</filename> and <filename>test/dstarmb1.root</filename> if you use a default location.
    		In the <filename>test/simple_test0.C</filename> file you have to change the following lines so that they
    		reflect your configuration (if default doesn't reflect your setup):
<programlisting>
set->Add( "root://depc218.gsi.de:20094//opt/PROOF_DATA/dstarmb0.root" );
set->Add( "root://depc218.gsi.de:20094//opt/PROOF_DATA/dstarmb1.root" );
</programlisting>
			Now you are ready to perform this test. Use the <xref linkend="How_to_run"/> to remote PROOF workers. As soon as you get
			required number of workers start a root session and execute the following command:
<screen>
<prompt>root [0] </prompt><command>.x test/simple_test0.C</command>
</screen>
			This macro will connect to the PROOF (POD's workers) workers and perform a test analysis.
   		</para>
		</sect1>
